<emphasis box="[151,213,1421,1444]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="306">Notes.</emphasis>
– This species is found throughout the Antilles, from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[214,294,1452,1476]" name="Mexico" pageId="17" pageNumber="306">Mexico</collectingCountry>
through Central America, across Caribbean 
<collectingCountry box="[113,224,1484,1508]" name="Venezuela" pageId="17" pageNumber="306">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
through the Guianas, and on the Pacific coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[113,224,1516,1540]" name="Colombia" pageId="17" pageNumber="306">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[236,328,1516,1540]" name="Ecuador" pageId="17" pageNumber="306">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[389,439,1517,1540]" name="Peru" pageId="17" pageNumber="306">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="TAYLOR" box="[457,614,1516,1540]" firstAuthor="TAYLOR" pageId="17" pageNumber="306" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). See 
<bibRefCitation author="TAYLOR" firstAuthor="TAYLOR" pageId="17" pageNumber="306" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR (2005)</bibRefCitation>
